	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64604313"><p>&gt;"Christie's Likens Microsoft's Work On MS-DOS To Einstein's Work In Physics"</p><p>Oh, total barf.  Christie's needs to take a class in computer history.  MS-DOS was essentially just a port/update of CP/M.  Both were super primitive compared to Unix.  Comparing that to ANY work of Einstein is disgusting.  At least Microsoft did something ACTUALLY interesting at the time, they licensed Unix to port as Xenix, which was also released before MS-DOS.</p><p>Also, at the time MS-DOS was released, Microware OS-9 was already developed and vastly superior.  And it ran on commodity hardware not long after.</p><p>The only thing MS-DOS really had going for it was the HUGE advantage of being in the IBM marketing/network/distribution umbrella.</p></div>
	</div>

