			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64604929"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64604929"><p><div class="quote"><p>Isn't DOS a clone of CP/M made by somebody who wasn't even working for MS at the time?</p></div><p>Yes. It was written by Tim Paterson at Seattle Computer Products.  It was bought from them by MS for peanuts (in a typical MS fraud - MS later settled with SCP out of court), and Paterson himself was poached to port it to the IBM PC.  It was written for the Intel 8086 processor but the IBM PC used the inferior 8088.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64604929">

