	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64604691">Everyone is an advancement of previous innovations.

Linux was inspired by Minix which was inspired by the various Unix implementations which was inspired by Multics and other previous work. The computer world is a complex interconnecting world of inspiration and forks. That's why copyright fascism and patent trolling is so bad in the computer world, because we are all reliant on each other. The GNU/Linux analogy also falls apart because modern Linux distros have thousands of packages from multiple organiza</div>
	</div>

